SENATE RESOLUTION 91
By Oliver
A RESOLUTION to recognize Teresa Agee on her selection as
the 2024–2025 Martin Luther King, Jr., School
High School Teacher of the Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this legislative body should pause to
specially recognize those outstanding teachers who have devoted their careers to providing the
highest-quality education for Tennessee's students; and
WHEREAS, Teresa Agee is one such estimable educator, who has distinguished herself
as a professional of the greatest dedication, ability, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, a teacher at Martin Luther King, Jr., School, Ms. Agee was recently named
the school's 2024–2025 High School Teacher of the Year, a most befitting honor for her tenure
as an educator, as it recognizes the positive influence she has on so many young lives; and
WHEREAS, Teresa Agee is an extremely talented and compassionate educator who
has worked assiduously throughout her career in education to motivate her students, fellow
teachers, and staff to reach their full potential as scholars, professionals, and citizens; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Agee truly serves as an inspiration to the faculty and staff at Martin
Luther King, Jr., School, and her friendship and counsel are highly valued by those who are
fortunate to know her; and
WHEREAS, Teresa Agee epitomizes the dedicated educator who is wholly committed to
the highest ideals of public service and quality education for all, and she should be specially
recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we hereby honor and
congratulate Teresa Agee on being chosen as the 2024–2025 Martin Luther King, Jr., School
